# AI-Assisted Workflow Portfolio

This repository documents how I use AI tools to structure business, content and research workflows.

The aim is to create a lightweight portfolio showing how AI can support research, planning, content production, documentation and commercial workflows in a practical business context.

## Purpose

I use this repository to organise and document AI-assisted workflows that can support:

- Healthcare and healthtech market research
- Business development and commercial planning
- Short-form content strategy
- Prompt development for AI media tools
- Resource pages, affiliate links and simple digital product planning
- Workflow documentation for repeatable processes

This is not a software engineering portfolio. It is a business and operations-focused AI workflow portfolio.

## How I plan to use Claude with this repository

I plan to connect this GitHub repository to Claude so that Claude can help review, improve and organise the workflow documentation.

Example use cases:

- Review existing workflow documents and suggest improvements
- Turn rough ideas into structured process documents
- Improve content planning systems
- Help organise prompt libraries
- Suggest clearer documentation for business workflows
- Support research notes and commercial planning
- Help refine audience journeys from content to resource links or digital products

The goal is to use Claude as an AI assistant for workflow thinking, documentation and process improvement.

## Current workflow areas

### 1. AI content workflow

A system for planning and producing short-form educational content using AI tools.

This includes:

- Audience and niche definition
- Pain point research
- Competitor content pattern review
- Hook and script development
- Visual prompt creation
- Talking-avatar or voiceover planning
- Editing and publishing workflow
- Performance review

### 2. AI media prompt development

A prompt library for image, video and avatar workflows.

Prompt structures may include:

- Subject
- Scene
- Camera angle
- Lighting
- Mood
- Movement
- Platform format
- Realism and safety notes

### 3. Content-to-resource journey

A simple structure for connecting educational content to useful next steps.

This may include:

- Resource pages
- Affiliate links where relevant
- Simple digital products
- Lead magnets
- Audience feedback loops
- Performance-based content improvement

### 4. Business and research workflows

A practical system for using AI to support business tasks such as:

- Company research
- Market mapping
- Sales preparation
- CRM follow-up planning
- Outreach message drafting
- Meeting preparation
- Workflow documentation

## Tool stack

### AI and strategy

- ChatGPT for strategy, scripting, prompt development and workflow planning
- Claude for reviewing documentation, improving structure and supporting process thinking

### AI media and content production

- HeyGen for talking-avatar workflows
- Kling for image-to-video and motion prompts
- Canva for content organisation and digital product design
- CapCut for editing, subtitles and short-form formatting

### Resource and monetisation layer

- Beacon for landing pages, resource pages and digital product delivery
- Affiliate platforms for relevant product links and recommendations

### Workflow organisation

- GitHub for documenting workflows, prompt libraries and repeatable processes

